summary: A set of Django model definitions used in the test suite to exercise admin raw‑ID widget behavior and provide simple data structures for various test scenarios, including many‑to‑many and foreign‑key relations to unregistered models, self‑referencing links, custom managers, and basic entities like albums, bands, cars, inventory, schools, and user profiles.
business_intent: Support automated testing of the Django admin interface, particularly the handling of raw ID widgets when related models are not registered, while also supplying lightweight example models for broader test coverage of model interactions and string representations.
